cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with image classification using a deep learning approach, specifically sparse coding and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of regularization and optimization techniques, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The use of neural networks also suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category. Finally, the paper involves experiments with image databases, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
